28/08/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- An earthquake measuring 4.4 on the Richter scale was detected in Athens at 7:35am local time Tuesday (August 28th), the Athens Geodynamic Institute announced. The epicentre of the earthquake was 45km north of the capital, in Avlida. No casualties or damage have been reported. 
On Monday, a tremor measuring 4 on the Richter scale struck at 6:30 pm local time in Patras, on the northern part of the Peloponnese peninsula. Earlier, a 5.1-magnitute earthquake shook the island of Kefalonia in western Greece. The epicentre of that one was in the sea, off the western coast of the island. (Naftemporiki, NewsIn - 28/08/07; AP - 27/08/07)
